# Gander — Website Checklist

Living checklist for public-facing site pages and content. Not in active build scope yet — capture requirements here as they come up.

## Legal & support pages

### Privacy (`/privacy`)

- [x] Create route: `app/privacy/page.tsx`
- [ ] Write privacy policy content (data collected, location, photos, retention, third parties)
- [ ] Cover Supabase auth, profile data, and future location/messaging features
- [x] Add “Last updated” date
- [x] Link from login page footer and/or settings

### Terms of service (`/terms`)

- [x] Create route: `app/terms/page.tsx`
- [ ] Write terms content (eligibility 18+, acceptable use, account termination)
- [x] Add “Last updated” date
- [x] Link from login page footer and/or settings

### FAQs (`/faqs`)

- [x] Create route: `app/faqs/page.tsx`
- [ ] Draft FAQ sections (account, profile, safety, how the app works)
- [x] Link from login page footer and/or help entry point in app

## Login page layout

- [x] Two-column layout: form left, hero video right (`app/page.tsx`)
- [x] Hero video component — drop file at `public/hero.mp4` (`components/login-hero-video.tsx`)
- [x] Site footer with FAQs, Privacy, Terms links (`components/site-footer.tsx`)

## Cross-cutting (when these pages ship)

- [x] Shared public layout or simple prose styling (rose/zinc palette, readable typography)
- [x] Footer or link block on `/` pointing to Privacy, Terms, FAQs
- [x] Page metadata (`title`, `description`) for each route
- [ ] Legal review before launch (not a substitute for a lawyer)

## Notes

- Routes should be **public** — no auth required; confirm `proxy.ts` does not redirect them
- Keep copy in components or markdown files so updates do not require layout changes
